The paper deals with automated typeface generation through image style transfer, which involves computer vision techniques such as image processing, feature extraction, and deep learning. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a Hierarchical Adversarial Network (HAN) for typeface transformation, which involves generative models and adversarial training, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also discusses the use of a hierarchical structure for the discriminator, which involves graph theory and network architecture, making cs.GR (Graphics) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with Chinese characters, which involves natural language processing and text analysis, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) a possible sub-category as well.
